Using Oracle 11g, when doing an in-place upgrade from 6.1.5 to 6.2.1, on the first start of the 6.2.1 application the automatic database modifications causes ORA-1408 :

{code:java}
localhost-startStop-1 ERROR      [core.entity.jdbc.DatabaseUtil] SQL Exception while executing the following:
CREATE INDEX idx_audit_item_log_id2 ON audit_item (LOG_ID)
Error was: java.sql.SQLException: ORA-01408: such column list already indexed
{code}

Then, later, the upgradetask_6256 delete the offending "idx_audit_item_log_id" index.

The idx_audit_item_log_id2 will be created during the next restart of Jira.

It would have been helpful to find this information in the "upgrade notes" for the 6.2.1 version, as seeing an Oracle error in the upgrade logs is very worrying :-)

