According to the {{issuelink}} REST [documentation|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/6.3/#d2e2018] is only applicable to the linking issue within the same JIRA server not remote server. Moreover, {{remotelink}} is only provide one way linking from JIRA A to B.

For example, 
JIRA B is showing JIRA A web issue link but the JIRA A issue links is not showing in JIRA B.

*Workaround to create remote issue links:*
# Run the REST call below:
{code}
curl -D- -u <username>:<password> -X POST -H "Content-type: application/json" --data @data.json {BASE-URL}/rest/api/2/issue/{ISSUE-KEY}/remotelink
{code}
# JSON data:
{code}
{
    "globalId": "appId=<Application-ID>&issueId=<ISSUE-KEY>",  //target instance
    "application": {                                            
         "application.type":"com.atlassian.jira",
         "application.name":"<target-application-name>",
         "url":"{BASE-URL}/browse/{ISSUE-KEY}",     
         "title":"<ISSUE-KEY>"                    
    },
    "relationship":"duplicates",                           
    "object": {        
        "application.type":"com.atlassian.jira",  //source instance
        "application.name":"<source-application-name>",                                   
        "url":"{BASE-URL}/browse/{ISSUE-KEY}",    
        "title":"{ISSUE-KEY}"

    }
}
{code}
(i) To get the {{Application-ID}}, please run the REST command below and look for the application id:
{code}
curl -s -X GET -u <user>:<pass> -H "Accept: application/json" <hostname>/rest/applinks/1.0/listApplicationlinks | python -mjson.tool
{code}

